claim.claim-text:
20. A method of creating an ice surface comprising the steps of: 
a) providing a source of water; 
b) heating said water; 
c) pressurizing said heated water; 
d) forcing said pressurized heated water through one or more nozzles sized and shaped to create a mist of fine droplets; and 
e) directing said droplets onto a surface to be coated with ice.
